// 🔁 2. Rearrangement / In-place manipulation
//* Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array

//PROBLEM STATEMENT---


/*

Problem
Chef is given a sorted array nums (non-decreasing order).
He wants to remove all duplicate elements in-place such that each element appears only once.
The relative order must remain the same.
After removing duplicates, let the number of unique elements be K.
The first K elements of the array should contain the unique elements.
Elements beyond K do not matter.
Your task is to find K and print the first K elements.

Function Declaration
Function Name: removeDuplicates
Description:
Removes duplicates from a sorted array in-place.

Parameters
nums → sorted array of integers

Return Value
Returns an integer K → number of unique elements
First K positions of the array should contain the unique elements

Constraints
1 ≤ N ≤ 3 × 10⁴
-100 ≤ nums[i] ≤ 100
Array is sorted in non-decreasing order

Input Format
First line contains integer N — size of array
Second line contains N space-separated sorted integers

Output Format
First print K
Then print first K unique elements

Sample Input 1
6
1 1 2 2 3 3

Sample Output 1
3
1 2 3

Explanation

Array: 1 1 2 2 3 3
After removing duplicates:
1 2 3 _ _ _
Unique elements = 3
First K elements = 1 2 3

Sample Input 2
5
0 0 1 1 1

Sample Output 2
2
0 1

Explanation

Array: 0 0 1 1 1
After removing duplicates:
0 1 _ _ _
Unique elements = 2
First K elements = 0 1

*/

//SOLUTION----

/*

    public static int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {
        if (nums.length == 0) return 0;

        int j = 0; // pointer for unique elements
        for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (nums[i] != nums[j]) {
                j++;
                nums[j] = nums[i];
            }
        }
        return j + 1; // count of unique elements
    }

*/
